{title}RML Student Tutorial - Learn Easy Web Development!{.title}

{success}Welcome to your first RML lesson! This tutorial will teach you everything step by step.{.success}

{lesson}
{subtitle}Lesson 1: What is RML?{.subtitle}

{text}RML stands for {bold}RazzMarkupLanguage{.bold}. It's like HTML but much easier to learn and use! Instead of confusing brackets like {code}<h1>{.code}, we use simple curly braces like {code}{title}{.code}.{.text}

{info}RML was created specifically for students who want to learn web development without getting overwhelmed by complex syntax.{.info}

{question}Why is RML easier than HTML?{.question}
{answer}
- Uses simple English words like {code}title{.code} instead of {code}h1{.code}
- Clear closing tags with dots: {code}{.title}{.code}
- No confusing angle brackets {code}< >{.code}
- Beginner-friendly tag names
{.answer}
{.lesson}

{lesson}
{subtitle}Lesson 2: Basic Text Tags{.subtitle}

{text}Let's learn the most important text tags first:{.text}

{exercise}
{bold}Try This Exercise:{.bold}
Copy this code and save it as {code}exercise1.rml{.code}:

{code}
{title}My First Webpage{.title}
{subtitle}About Me{.subtitle}
{text}Hi! I'm learning RML and it's really fun!{.text}
{bold}This text is bold{.bold}
{italic}This text is italic{.italic}
{underline}This text is underlined{.underline}
{.code}
{.exercise}

{note}Remember: Every opening tag like {code}{title}{.code} needs a closing tag like {code}{.title}{.code} with a dot!{.note}
{.lesson}

{lesson}
{subtitle}Lesson 3: Lists and Links{.subtitle}

{text}Lists help organize information. Links connect to other pages.{.text}

{example}
{bold}Example: Making a list{.bold}
{code}
{list}
    {item}First thing{.item}
    {item}Second thing{.item}
    {item}Third thing{.item}
{.list}
{.code}

{bold}Example: Making a link{.bold}
{code}
{link href="https://www.google.com"}Click here to visit Google{.link}
{.code}
{.example}

{exercise}
{bold}Your Turn!{.bold}
Create a list of your three favorite:
1. Foods
2. Movies  
3. Games

Then add a link to your favorite website!
{.exercise}
{.lesson}

{lesson}
{subtitle}Lesson 4: Special Message Boxes{.subtitle}

{text}RML has special tags that create colorful message boxes:{.text}

{success}This is a success message - use it when something goes right!{.success}

{warning}This is a warning message - use it to alert users about something important!{.warning}

{error}This is an error message - use it when something goes wrong!{.error}

{info}This is an info message - use it to share helpful information!{.info}

{tip}This is a tip message - use it to give helpful advice!{.tip}

{note}This is a note message - use it for additional information!{.note}

{example}
{code}
{success}You did great!{.success}
{warning}Don't forget to save your file!{.warning}
{error}Something went wrong!{.error}
{info}Here's some useful information.{.info}
{tip}Pro tip: Always test your code!{.tip}
{note}Remember to backup your work.{.note}
{.code}
{.example}
{.lesson}

{lesson}
{subtitle}Lesson 5: Educational Tags{.subtitle}

{text}RML has special tags perfect for homework, quizzes, and lessons:{.text}

{homework}
{bold}Homework Assignment{.bold}
{text}Create a webpage about yourself using at least 5 different RML tags.{.text}

{question}What should you include?{.question}
{answer}
- Your name as a title
- A paragraph about yourself
- A list of hobbies
- A link to something you like
- At least one special message box
{.answer}
{.homework}

{quiz}
{bold}Quick Quiz{.bold}

{question}1. What symbol do we put before closing tag names?{.question}
{answer}A dot (.) - Example: {code}{.title}{.code}{.answer}

{question}2. Which tag makes text bold?{.question}
{answer}The {code}{bold}{.code} tag{.answer}

{question}3. How do you create a link?{.question}
{answer}{code}{link href="url"}Link text{.link}{.code}{.answer}
{.quiz}
{.lesson}

{lesson}
{subtitle}Lesson 6: Images and Media{.subtitle}

{text}Adding pictures and videos makes your webpage more interesting!{.text}

{example}
{bold}Adding an image:{.bold}
{code}
{image src="my-photo.jpg" alt="A photo of me"}
{.code}

{bold}Adding a video:{.bold}
{code}
{video src="my-video.mp4"}My cool video{.video}
{.code}
{.example}

{tip}Always add {code}alt="description"{.code} to images so people with screen readers know what the image shows!{.tip}
{.lesson}

{lesson}
{subtitle}Lesson 7: Page Layout{.subtitle}

{text}Use these tags to organize your page layout:{.text}

{container}
{bold}Container Box{.bold}
{text}This is inside a container - it's like a box that holds other content.{.text}
{.container}

{card}
{bold}Card Box{.bold}
{text}Cards are special containers that look nice and stand out from the rest of the page.{.text}
{.card}

{section}
{bold}Section{.bold}
{text}Sections help divide your page into different parts, like chapters in a book.{.text}
{.section}

{example}
{code}
{header}
    {title}My Website{.title}
    {navigation}Menu goes here{.navigation}
{.header}

{main}
    {section}
        {subtitle}About Me{.subtitle}
        {text}Main content goes here{.text}
    {.section}
{.main}

{footer}
    {text}Copyright 2024{.text}
{.footer}
{.code}
{.example}
{.lesson}

{lesson}
{subtitle}Lesson 8: Shortcuts for Faster Typing{.subtitle}

{text}RML has shortcuts that make typing even faster:{.text}

{info}You can use these shortcuts instead of full tag names:{.info}

{table}
{row}
    {headercell}Shortcut{.headercell}
    {headercell}Full Version{.headercell}
    {headercell}Result{.headercell}
{.row}
{row}
    {cell}**bold**{.cell}
    {cell}{code}{bold}bold{.bold}{.code}{.cell}
    {cell}{bold}bold{.bold}{.cell}
{.row}
{row}
    {cell}*italic*{.cell}
    {cell}{code}{italic}italic{.italic}{.code}{.cell}
    {cell}{italic}italic{.italic}{.cell}
{.row}
{row}
    {cell}__underline__{.cell}
    {cell}{code}{underline}underline{.underline}{.code}{.cell}
    {cell}{underline}underline{.underline}{.cell}
{.row}
{row}
    {cell}`code`{.cell}
    {cell}{code}{code}code{.code}{.code}{.cell}
    {cell}{code}code{.code}{.cell}
{.row}
{row}
    {cell}- item{.cell}
    {cell}{code}{item}item{.item}{.code}{.cell}
    {cell}â€¢ item{.cell}
{.row}
{.table}
{.lesson}

